ARK LEARNING MANAGEMENT SYSTEM (TEACHER-CENTERED)

MAIN OBJECTIVES:
- To eliminate material distribution inefficiencies and submission management chaos through the design and implementation of a 
  centralized digital repository and automated tracking system that organizes learning materials by academic period, 
  enables digital submission tracking across sections, and provides real-time visibility of assignment status. 
- To reduce excessive assessment creation workload and address the critical lack of supplemental learning materials through 
  the integration of AI-powered instructional support tools that automate diverse question generation, analyze content quality, 
  and generate adaptive learning materials.     
- To automate student progress monitoring and enable early intervention through the development of intelligent monitoring systems 
  that identify at-risk students based on performance baselines and provide data-driven insights into assignment effectiveness.                                                                                
- To resolve platform usability failures through the creation of customized role-specific dashboards that consolidate fragmented 
  workflows into unified, intuitive interfaces for both teaching personnel and students.    

 (1) CENTRALIZED DIGITAL REPOSITORY and AUTOMATED TRACKING SYSTEM
     ~organizes learning materials by academic period
     ~enables digital submission tracking across sections   
     ~provides real-time visibilty of assignment status

 (2) INTEGRATION OF AI-POWERED INSTRUCTIONAL SUPPORT TOOLS 
     ~automate diverse question generation
     ~analyze content quality
     ~generate adoptive learning materials

 (3) DEVELOMENT OF INTELLIGENT MONITORING SYSTEM
     ~identifies at-risk students based on performance baselines
     ~provide data-driven insights into assigment effectiveness     

 (4) CREATION OF CUSTOMIZED ROLE-SPECIFIC DASHBOARDS 
     ~consolidate fragmented workflows into unified, intuitive interface for both teachers and students

