Think of yourself as a Senior UI/UX Designer and a Full-Stack Developer specializing in Next.js 14 (App Router), Supabase, and Tailwind CSS.

Project Overview:
We'll be building a Learning Management System (LMS) called Arkadian LMS (ALMS).
    Tech Stack: Next.js (pnpm), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Standard CSS, Supabase (Auth, DB, Storage).
    Authentication: Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD) integrated via Supabase Auth.
    User Roles: Admin, Teacher, Student.

Task:
Help me architect and build the Main Landing Page and the Authentication Flow (use STI's main page as a reference above, I'll later modify it). 
Specifically, I need to integrate Microsoft Entra so that the Admin can create and manage accounts in Entra, and users can sign in via the LMS.
System Requirements & User Roles:
    Admin Flow: * Creates/provides accounts for Teachers and Students via Microsoft Entra.
        Data must sync/persist in a Supabase profiles table.
        Dashboard includes: User analytics (Total students/teachers) and management tables.
    Teacher Flow (UX Reference: Google Classroom):
        Creates Classes (Name, Section, Semester).
        Generates/shares "Invitation Codes" for students to join.
        Uploads modules, creates activities/quizzes with due dates (calendar sync).
        Manages a Gradebook (auto-checked quizzes + manual grading for essays).
    Student Flow:
        Joins classes via codes.
        Accesses learning materials and submits assignments.
        Takes quizzes within the system.
UI/UX Specifications (Shared Layout): (I'll provide some photos for the sidebar reference)
    Top Navigation Bar:
        Left: Collapse Sidebar Icon + Dynamic Page Title (e.g., "Dashboard").
        Right: Notification icon + Profile (Avatar generated by initials, Full Name, and Username).
    Sidebar Navigation:
        Header: "Ark" Logo + Institution Name.
        Sections: "Overview" (Dashboard) and "Management" (Role-specific links).
        Behavior: Collapsible to icons-only view.

Current Project State:
    Project initialized with pnpm create next-app@latest.
    Supabase is running locally (status: local development setup running).
    Goal for this session: Focus on setting up the Microsoft Entra login logic and the responsive Top Nav/Sidebar layout that changes based on the user's role.

